be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">“ad-free” it’s TV</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">especially </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">radi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">o </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">channels</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> are awash with annoying, repeated ad’s for it’s own programmes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">By this mechanism the BBC could save greatly on the costs of evasion, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">plus </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">it’s </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">substantial </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">funding </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">(private) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">TVL–Capita</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> enforcement.  This would also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">re</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">move</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">much criticised </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">elements of public har</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">as</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ment </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and threats, widely reported, and avoid </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">people </span><span style